      <h2>Fagor Industrial — Spanish Onnera Group, Mondragón Cooperative heritage</h2>
      <p>
        Fagor Industrial is the commercial foodservice equipment division of Spain's Onnera Group, which carries
        the cooperative heritage of the Mondragón Corporation — Spain's largest industrial cooperative federation.
        The commercial dishwasher line spans undercounter, door, hood, pass-through, rack-conveyor, and flight-type
        configurations, plus specialty utensil washers and heat-recovery ventless models. Fagor Industrial continues
        to operate as a going concern under Onnera Group with active R&amp;D and growing US distribution.
      </p>
      <p>
        The critical distinction for LA buyers: Fagor Industrial is NOT Fagor Electrodomésticos. Fagor
        Electrodomésticos was the residential white-goods brand that went bankrupt in 2013 and was subsequently
        acquired by Brandt. They are separate companies with separate ownership histories. A lot of search results
        and general web content conflates the two — you'll see "Fagor bankrupt" or "Fagor out of business"
        references that stem from the 2013 residential story but don't apply to the commercial dishwasher business.
        Your Fagor commercial dishwasher is serviceable, parts flow, new models ship.
      </p>
      <p>
        US distribution runs through Hart+Price (hartprice.com), the primary Fagor Industrial US distributor, plus
        Fagor Commercial USA for direct warranty support and bi-lingual English/Spanish service coordination. The
        bi-lingual support is meaningful in LA, where a significant share of the commercial foodservice industry
        is Spanish-language-first in the back-of-house.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

