  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Fagor Industrial vs Fagor Electrodomésticos — the 2013 disambiguation</h2>
      <p>
        This deserves its own section because it's a persistent source of confusion in the LA market. In 2013,
        Fagor Electrodomésticos — the Basque residential white-goods cooperative (refrigerators, washing machines,
        residential dishwashers, residential ovens) — went bankrupt as part of the broader 2008-2013 Spanish
        economic crisis impact. Groupe Brandt acquired portions of the residential operations afterwards.
      </p>
      <p>
        Fagor Industrial — the commercial foodservice equipment division — was a separate business under a separate
        corporate structure within the broader Mondragón Corporation cooperative network. Fagor Industrial did NOT
        go bankrupt. It continued operating, subsequently reorganized into the Onnera Group umbrella, and today
        remains an active Spanish commercial foodservice manufacturer with ongoing US distribution.
      </p>
      <p>
        For LA operators looking at search results that reference "Fagor bankruptcy": unless the specific reference
        is to Electrodomésticos (residential appliances), it's confused or outdated content. Your commercial Fagor
        dishwasher is a product of a company that's still operating, still shipping parts, and still supported.
        We service Fagor commercial regularly in LA and have no parts-supply concerns for current-production lines.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

